REPUTATION AND FACTION SYSTEM

Your reputation tracks how various factions of Rifts Earth view you.
Actions in the game world affect your standing with different groups.

COMMAND
  reputation            shows your current faction standings
  wanted                shows your infamy score with the CS

FACTIONS
  Coalition States (CS)
    The dominant military power on Rifts North America.  They view D-Bees
    and magic users as existential threats.  Killing CS soldiers raises
    your CS infamy.  High infamy causes CS soldiers to attack on sight.

  Praxis Citizens
    The survivors and settlers of Praxis Refuge.  Helping them with quests
    improves your standing.

  Lazlo
    The academic city-state to the north, friendly to D-Bees and mages.
    Completed quests involving helping people often improve Lazlo standing.

INFAMY
  CS infamy is tracked separately via the 'wanted' command.  High infamy
  (50+) marks you as wanted.  CS Dead Boys will attack you on sight.
  Infamy decays slowly over time.

REPUTATION EFFECTS
  Your reputation affects NPC dialogue, quest availability, and whether
  certain NPCs will attack you on entry to their area.

